ason": null, "body": "The lang team [indicated](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/104087#issuecomment-1324173328) that the following code should compile:\r\n```rust\r\nconst unsafe fn test() -> usize { 42 }\r\n\r\nfn main() { unsafe {\r\n    let x = [0; test()];\r\n} }\r\n```\r\nHowever currently the array length does not \"inherit\" unsafety from the surrounding block.\r\n```\r\nerror[E0133]: call to unsafe function is unsafe and requires unsafe function or block\r\n --> src/main.rs:4:17\r\n  |\r\n4 |     let x = [0; test()];\r\n  |                 ^^^^^^ call to unsafe function\r\n  |\r\n  = note: consult the function's documentation for information on how to avoid undefined behavior\r\n```", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/105204/reactions", "total_count": 1, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 1, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/105204/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}